title: Cactus Plant Flea Market x Swarovski x Dunk Low 'Pure Platinum'
description: Designed in partnership with the L.A.-based streetwear brand, the Cactus Plant Flea Market x Swarovski x Nike Dunk Low ‘Pure Platinum’ delivers an opulent take on the classic silhouette. Every inch of the suede upper is entirely covered in Swarovski crystals, including the detachable double lace flaps, heavily padded tongue and oversized Swoosh, the latter borrowed from CPFM’s previous Nike Blazer collaboration from 2019.

title: SB Dunk Low “Grateful Dead - Green Bear”
description: The Grateful Dead x Nike SB Dunk Low “Green Bear” is one of three extremely sought after colorways from the California based rock band’s collaboration with Nike SB. Nike SB produced a swarm of exciting new and original designs in 2020 that incorporate elements outside of the realm of sneaker culture, with the trio of Grateful Dead Dunks heading the lineup. The two-toned appearance of the upper features green faux fur on the toe, mid-panel, and heel as a direct reference to the band’s marching bears characters commonly seen on various artworks for Grateful Dead albums and merchandise. The motif reappears in a multicolor design on the insole. Tonal suede overlays dot the forefoot, eyelets, and heel. Branding appears in the form of a contrasting blue jagged Swoosh on the mid-panel, blue Nike embroidery on the heel, and a mini marching bear and Swoosh logo inside of an emblem on the tongue. One final detail of note, the hidden stash pocket located on the inside of the tongue displays the band's "Steal Your Face" skull.

title: Carpet Company x Dunk High SB
description: The Carpet Company x Nike Dunk High SB represents the Swoosh’s first collaboration with the Baltimore skate brand, founded in 2015 by a pair of brothers, Ayman and Osama Abdeldayem. Their take on the retro high-top features a white leather upper with semi-translucent blue overlays, inspired by screen printing and designed to wear away with prolonged use. Underneath the fabric, a yellow leather base is accented with a series of whimsical graphics. Additional tearaway detailing on the back heel reveals hidden Carpet Company branding, joining the label’s embroidered star logo on the lateral heel and a Carpet wordmark on the rubber outsole.

title: Wmns Dunk Low 'Orange Pearl'
description: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Orange Pearl’ offers a pastel colorway of the classic low-top, rendered in traditional color blocking in keeping with the shoe’s ‘80s roots. The upper carries a stark white base with contrasting overlays in a pale coral hue. Traditional Dunk details include a perforated toe box and a lightly padded nylon tongue marked with a woven Nike tag. The sneaker is supported by a two-tone rubber cupsole, equipped with a basketball-specific traction pattern made for pivoting.

title: Dunk High SE 'All Star 2021'
description: Celebrating the NBA’s midseason break, the Nike Dunk High ‘All Star 2021’ delivers an eye-catching two-tone colorway of the retro hoops shoe. The upper combines a pistachio-hued leather base with contrasting patent leather overlays in a glossy black finish. A standard Nike woven tag decorates the tongue, while an NBA All-Star emblem is stitched onto the lateral heel. The high-top is mounted on a standard rubber cupsole, featuring a pivot-ready traction pattern originally designed for the hardwood.

title: Dunk Low 'Black White'
description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Black White’ treats the retro model to an essential two-tone color scheme that accentuates the sneaker’s clean lines, developed by designer Peter Moore and responsible for the shoe’s easy transition from the hardwood to the street. The leather upper combines a white base with contrasting black overlays that wrap around the toe and heel. On both the woven tongue tag and heel tab, Nike branding in white stands out in relief against a black backdrop.

title: Supreme x Dunk Low OG SB QS 'Black'
description: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Black’ represents an homage to the partner brands’ Dunk High release from 2003. The low-top brings back virtually every key feature of the older shoe, including a white leather base, printed gold stars and contrast-colored overlays in croc-embossed leather. Gold Nike hits at the heel tab and woven tongue tag are matched by a gilded Supreme lace jewel. Inside the shoe, Supreme and Nike SB branding decorates the custom sockliner, finished in a bold red hue and fitted with a Zoom Air unit for lightweight cushioning.

title: Supreme x Dunk Low OG SB QS 'Barkroot Brown'
description: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Barkroot Brown’ features a familiar design inspired by the brands’ Dunk High collaboration from 2003, released during the height of the Silver Box era. Like the original, the shoe features a white leather upper, printed gold stars, stuffed textile tongue, flat black laces, a gold Supreme lace jewel, and croc-embossed leather overlays, finished here in a rich brown hue. Inside the shoe, dual Supreme and Nike SB branding decorates the red sockliner, featuring a Zoom Air unit in the heel for responsive cushioning.

title: Dunk High Premium 'Dark Curry'
description: The Nike Dunk High Premium ‘Dark Curry’ showcases warm, autumnal tones on a sneaker that began as a performance hoops shoe in 1985 and re-emerged decades later as a streetwear staple. The high-top features a Velvet Brown suede upper with a burnt orange Swoosh and shaggy suede overlays in Dark Russet. The sneaker is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, undergirded by a traction pattern made for pivoting on the hardwood.

title: Supreme x Dunk Low OG SB QS 'Hyper Royal'
description: The Supreme x Nike Dunk Low OG SB QS ‘Hyper Royal’ takes direct inspiration from the New York skate brand’s Dunk High collaboration from 2003. Like the high-top, this pair features a white leather base with metallic gold stars on the quarter panels and croc-embossed leather overlays in a contrasting hue. A standard Nike wordmark is embroidered in gold lettering on the heel tab, matching the woven tag atop the stuffed textile tongue. A gold Supreme dubrae shines at the bottom of the lace bed. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Zoom Air-infused sockliner, its crimson surface embellished with dual Supreme and Nike SB branding.

title: Dunk Low SP 'UNLV' 2021
description: The 2021 reissue of the Nike Dunk Low SP ‘UNLV’ revives one of the original colorways of the 1985 ‘Be True to Your School’ series, albeit in low-top form. The sneaker is rendered in the signature colors of the University of Las Vegas, highlighted by a neutral grey leather base with contrasting University Red overlays. A padded collar and breathable nylon tongue combine for a comfortable fit, the latter accented with a woven Nike tag in the same grey and red color scheme.

title: Dunk Low 'Hyper Cobalt'
description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Hyper Cobalt’ could be mistaken for an original 1985 colorway, featuring OG-style two-tone color blocking and a crisp white midsole. The leather upper combines a black base with contrasting blue overlays and a matching signature Swoosh. Traditional branding hits take the form of a woven Nike tongue tag, an embroidered Nike wordmark on the heel tab, and a Nike logo stamped on the sockliner in an unexpected pop of orange coloring.
